title: Appointments to Advisory Council on Food and Environmental Hygiene announced
content_text:
p>
          The Government today (March 22) announced that the Chief Executive had 
          re-appointed Mr Felix Fong Wo as the Chairman of the Advisory Council 
          on Food and Environmental Hygiene for a term of two years with effect 
          from April 1, 2013. Mr Fong is a lawyer and has been the Chairman of 
          the Council since 2009. At the same time, four new members were appointed and 11 serving 
          members were re-appointed to the Council. All of the appointments are

members were re-appointed to the Council. All of the appointments are 
          for a term of two years from April 1, 2013, to March 31, 2015. The four new members are Mr Abraham Chan Yu-ling, Dr Chung Shan-shan, 
          Ms Josephine Kea Chi-shun and Dr Kenneth Leung Mei-yee. Mr Abraham Chan Yu-ling is Chairman and CEO of PuraPharm Group of 
          Companies, a manufacturer of Chinese medicine and health products. Dr Chung Shan-shan is an Assistant Professor in the Department of

Biology and the Programme Director for the Master of Science in 
          Environmental and Public Health Management of the Hong Kong Baptist 
          University. Ms Josephine Kea Chi-shun is the Principal of the Hong Kong Institute 
          of Vocational Education (Chai Wan) and the Academic Director of the 
          Vocational Training Council Business Administration Discipline. Dr Kenneth Leung Mei-yee is an Associate Professor in the School of 
          Biological Science and the Programme Director for Master of Science in

Biological Science and the Programme Director for Master of Science in 
          Environmental Management of the University of Hong Kong. Welcoming the new appointments, the Secretary for Food and Health, Dr 
          Ko Wing-man, said he believed the Council would be able to benefit 
          from their wise counsel and expertise when tendering advice to the 
          Government on food and environmental hygiene issues. Dr Ko also expressed gratitude to the four outgoing members, Mr Ronald 
          Lau Yiu-fai, Mrs Elizabeth Mok Lee Mi-yu, Professor Rudolf Wu Shiu-sun

and Dr Yue Kwok-to, for their valuable contribution to the work of the 
          Council. All of them had served on the Council for six years. "In the past few years, the Council has provided valuable advice to 
          the Government on a wide range of weighty issues including measures 
          against avian influenza and human swine influenza, as well as 
          legislative proposals on food safety, nutrition labelling and formula 
          products intended for infants and young children. The Government will 
          continue to look to the Council for advice on food and environmental

continue to look to the Council for advice on food and environmental hygiene issues", Dr Ko said. The Council is a non-statutory body established on April 1, 2000, to advise the Government on food and environmental hygiene issues. The Council comprises a Chairman, 15 non-official members and four ex-officio members. The new membership list of the Council with effect from April 1, 2013, is as follows: Chairman
